subSubSection.paragraph:
The well-supported sister relationship of 

Fenerivieae

and 

Maasieae

is reported herein for the first time (
Fig. 1
). The two tribes share a number of features, e.g., axillary inflorescences, generally one ovule per ovary, and spiniform endosperm ruminations (

MOLS
et al., 2008

; 
SAUNDERS et al., 2011
). Their possible closest relationships were previously discussed (
SCHATZ & LE THOMAS, 1990
; 
SAUNDERS et al., 2011
).

